title: Data_Analysis_II_Notes
text:
Here are some git commands I never remember:

git add .
git commit -m “comment”
git push origin main
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/KingBlkMouth/Data_Analysis_II_Notes.git
git remote -v
git remote show origin

Here are some quarto commands:

quarto publish gh-pages



Push an existing repository from the command line:

git remote add origin https://github.com/KingBlkMouth/Data_Analysis_II_Notes.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

Setting up the website:

Create a new git repository
In that repo, view all branches -> New branch name it gh-pages.
Name the Quarto website the same as the repo
render the website
add the ignore paths to .gitignore
git remote add origin
git branch -M main
git add .
git commit
git push.
quarto publish
Quarto publish is all that needs to be done afterwards.
